content:
Manage the View of Data in a Values Table

The values table displays all columns in your dataset. You can customize the view by sorting row values using any column except for the index column.

On the left-hand side, measure and dimension tiles represent visible columns. To move a tile, click and hold it then drag to a new position. Release when the position indicator is correct. Click the x button to remove a measure or grouping from the table.

Click the pencil button to access the Edit Columns dialog and hide or show any column. Add, edit, or remove filters by clicking the relevant button. Sort rows by clicking a column's heading cell until an arrow appears in the desired direction.

When sorting, null records are excluded from the table. Assign a default value to prevent exclusion of null records.
title: Customizing Values Tables in Salesforce Analytics
